<b>Subject:</b> Re: Binding?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/mithaniel_marr.cgi?read=20" TARGET=_self>Binding?</A> (Mourn)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> My friend has wander across the desert of Ro

<BR>&gt; and would like to remain in my city.. So
<BR>&gt; when he dies he isn't transported all the
<BR>&gt; way back to the dreaded Innothule swamp..
<BR>&gt; we've heard of something called binding..
<BR>&gt; What is this how does it work?
<P>Binding is a spell that allows Wizards, Clerics
<BR>and not for sure about Enchanters or other
<BR>spell casters to BIND a person to the city
<BR>they are presently located. I know for clerics
<BR>they can bind them selves to anywhere but
<BR>have to bind others in a city. But also Clerics
<BR>do not get bind until level 14. Don't know about
<BR>the other spell casters.
<P>Hope this helps
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
